{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id8eeece67-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s527"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"527"},"text":"§ 527.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Purchases of implements of war, etc., from American Republics","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretaries of the Army and of the Navy are authorized to purchase arms, ammunition, and implements of war produced within the jurisdiction of any American republic if such arms, ammunition, or implements of war cannot be produced in the United States.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id8eeece68-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1940-06-15/ch365/s7"},"text":"June 15, 1940, ch. 365, § 7","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/54/397"},"text":"54 Stat. 397","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1947-07-26/ch343"},"text":"July 26, 1947, ch. 343","children":[],"tail":", title II, § 205(a), "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/61/501"},"text":"61 Stat. 501","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id8eeece69-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id8eeece6a-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"changeOfName","id":"id8eeece6b-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Change of Name","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Department of War designated Department of the Army and title of Secretary of War changed to Secretary of the Army by section 205(a) of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1947-07-26/ch343/tII"},"text":"act July 26, 1947, ch. 343, title II","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/61/501"},"text":"61 Stat. 501","children":[],"tail":". Section 205(a) of act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1947-07-26"},"text":"July 26, 1947","children":[],"tail":", was repealed by section 53 of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-08-10/ch1041"},"text":"act Aug. 10, 1956, ch. 1041","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70A/641"},"text":"70A Stat. 641","children":[],"tail":". Section 1 of act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1956-08-10"},"text":"Aug. 10, 1956","children":[],"tail":", enacted “Title 10, Armed Forces” which in sections 3010 to 3013 continued Department of the Army under administrative supervision of Secretary of the Army."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"execDoc","id":"id8eeece6c-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Executive Documents","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id8eeece6d-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Secretary of the Air Force","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For transfer of certain procurement and related functions and property, insofar as they pertain to Air Force, from Secretary of the Army and Department of the Army to Secretary of the Air Force and Department of the Air Force, see Secretary of Defense Transfer Order Nos. 6 [§ 1(a)(41)], eff. ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1948-01-15"},"text":"Jan. 15, 1948","children":[],"tail":"; 39 [§ 2zz], "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1949-05-18"},"text":"May 18, 1949","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
